This paper discusses a solution to reduce end-to-end delay in wireless communication systems, which is a common problem in the field of computer networks and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the implementation of a real-time system, which involves security and cryptography, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of a Markov decision process, which is a common technique in information theory and optimization, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible category. The paper also proposes a framework for decision-making, which involves control systems and decision-making algorithms, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the burden on the core network, which is a common problem in distributed systems, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible category.
